Package: sentinel-endpoint-security
Version: 1.0.0
Section: admin
Priority: optional
Architecture: amd64
Maintainer: CS-Fasih <cs.fasih@github.com>
Depends: clamav (>= 0.103), clamav-daemon (>= 0.103), libjson-c5 (>= 0.15), libpthread-stubs0-dev
Homepage: https://github.com/CS-Fasih/Endpoint-Security-Quarantine-Tool-for-Linux
Description: Sentinel â€” Real-Time Endpoint Security & Quarantine Tool
 Sentinel is a real-time endpoint security daemon for Linux that monitors
 the filesystem using inotify, scans new and modified files with ClamAV,
 and automatically quarantines detected threats.
 .
 Features:
  - Real-time file monitoring via inotify (recursive)
  - ClamAV integration via clamd UNIX socket
  - Automatic quarantine with UUID-based manifest tracking
  - Electron GUI dashboard with live scan log and threat vault
  - Secure IPC via UNIX domain sockets (no TCP exposure)
  - Thread pool for non-blocking parallel scans
  - Graceful inotify watch limit handling (ENOSPC)
  - State synchronization protocol for GUI reconnection
